        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:29PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ardmore, or 21 miles southeast of Edgemont, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ardmore.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
